.TH SINGINE-DOTFILES 1 "2026-03-22" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-dotfiles \- inspect and capture home dotfiles into a controlled repo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine dotfiles inspect
[\fB--home-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--dotfiles-repo\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine dotfiles dashboard
[\fB--home-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--dotfiles-repo\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--output-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine dotfiles capture
\fINAME\fR
[\fB--home-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--dotfiles-repo\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--json\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B singine dotfiles
is the first safe control layer for the personal dotfiles you named.
It inventories shell startup files, Vim config, Claude state, Logseq state,
Dropbox, and the controlled dotfiles repo.
.PP
Current targets include:
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.profile\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.bash_profile\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.bashrc\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.zprofile\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.zshrc\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.vimrc\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.box-shell\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.claude\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI.logseq\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fIDropbox\fR
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B inspect
Emit a JSON inventory of managed and unmanaged targets.
.TP
.B dashboard
Write an HTML dashboard and JSON report. Default output is under
.IR target/sindoc.local/dotfiles .
.TP
.B capture
Copy one file-backed target into the dotfiles repo or write a manifest for one
directory-backed target.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine dotfiles inspect --json

singine dotfiles dashboard \\
  --output-dir /Users/skh/ws/git/github/sindoc/singine/target/sindoc.local/dotfiles \\
  --json

singine dotfiles capture bashrc --json
singine dotfiles capture vimrc --json
singine dotfiles capture claude-home --json
singine dotfiles capture logseq-home --json
singine dotfiles capture dropbox --json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-man (1),
.BR singine-ai (1),
.BR singine-logseq (1),
.BR singine-template (1)
